tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/022-harness_adhere-task.log:1836:67:{"schema_version":"1.0.0","event_id":"019db7b5-225d-7142-924b-0a9d8affd58e","spec_id":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000c01","phase":"do-task","agent_session_id":"cli-session","timestamp":"2026-04-23T00:19:54.589977Z","origin_kind":"tool_primary","tool":"report_phase_outcome","payload":{"event_type":"phase_outcome_reported","spec_id":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000c01","phase":"do-task","agent_session_id":"cli-session","outcome":{"outcome":"complete","summary":"T02 complete: added docs/rewrite/PHASE0_BEHAVIOR_TRACEABILITY.json with stable BEH-P0-* mappings for scenarios 1.1-8.1, ownership, and positive/falsification obligations; added scripts/proof/phase0/validate_behavior_traceability.py; validator and just check both passed."}}}
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/022-harness_adhere-task.log:1991:        "body": "Behavior proof is expressed as executable `.feature` scenarios (cucumber-rs) tagged with a stable behavior ID (`@BEH-*`). Every in-scope behavior needs both a positive witness (scenario demonstrates the behavior) and a falsification witness (scenario demonstrates the inverse is rejected). Unit and integration tests via `nextest` remain in support of the scenario suite — they do not substitute for scenario ownership of a behavior ID."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/022-harness_adhere-task.log:2013:        "body": "Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/022-harness_adhere-task.log:2053:        "body": "Test suites are gated on mutation strength via `cargo-mutants`. Surviving mutants are treated as evidence of weak scenarios: each survivor must be triaged and resolved against a behavior ID (`BEH-*`) — either by tightening an existing scenario, adding a falsification scenario, or explicitly recording the mutant as equivalent with a linked justification. Mutation regressions fail the final gate; the staged `just` recipes surface mutant output in a machine-consumable form for triage."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/022-harness_adhere-task.log:2089:@phase0 @smoke @positive @BEH-P0-401
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/022-harness_adhere-task.log:2142:- Every behavior-owning scenario must include exactly one stable `@BEH-*` tag.
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/022-harness_adhere-task.log:2368:/bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n "@BEH-" tests/bdd -S' in /Users/trevor/Documents/GitHub/tanren
