tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/017-harness_do-task.log:4606:- PB-02 Phase 0 behavior inventory maps Feature 1.1 through 8.1 to stable behavior IDs and scenarios.
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/017-harness_do-task.log:4654:Behavior proof is expressed as executable `.feature` scenarios (cucumber-rs) tagged with a stable behavior ID (`@BEH-*`). Every in-scope behavior needs both a positive witness (scenario demonstrates the behavior) and a falsification witness (scenario demonstrates the inverse is rejected). Unit and integration tests via `nextest` remain in support of the scenario suite — they do not substitute for scenario ownership of a behavior ID.
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/017-harness_do-task.log:4673:Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate.
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/017-harness_do-task.log:4906:/bin/zsh -lc "find . -type f -name '*.feature' | sed -n '1,120p'; rg -n \"@BEH-|Feature:|Scenario:\" -g\"*.feature\" -S ." in /Users/trevor/Documents/GitHub/tanren
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/017-harness_do-task.log:4958:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/002-harness_do-task.log:1132:tanren/standards/rust-testing/behavior-traceability.md:17:Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate.
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/017-harness_do-task.log:4959:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/002-harness_do-task.log:1133:tanren/standards/rust-testing/bdd-scenarios.md:16:Behavior proof is expressed as executable `.feature` scenarios (cucumber-rs) tagged with a stable behavior ID (`@BEH-*`). Every in-scope behavior needs both a positive witness (scenario demonstrates the behavior) and a falsification witness (scenario demonstrates the inverse is rejected). Unit and integration tests via `nextest` remain in support of the scenario suite — they do not substitute for scenario ownership of a behavior ID.
